                            <comment id="14710467" author="prr" created="Fri, 4 Oct 2024 12:49:37 -0700"  >With a bit of DIY image processing, I can see that the images are nearly identical.&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;m attaching out1.png and out2.png which replaces the differing pixels with red and blue&lt;br/&gt;
In one row the standalone word &amp;quot;a&amp;quot; is moved a pixel to the right, but its actual rendering is identical, just shifted.&lt;br/&gt;
The image is 400x400 so 160,000 pixels.&lt;br/&gt;
There are only 85 pixels different across the entire image&lt;br/&gt;
There are 3457 non-white pixels in each image since it is mostly white.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe we could add a tolerance that the number of differences must be less&lt;br/&gt;
than 5% of the non-white pixels, which in this would be about 0.05% of the total image.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I don&amp;#39;t know what is so different about SLES but text rotation differences seem to affect SLES and nowhere else.&lt;br/&gt;
See for example&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8219641&quot;&gt;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8219641&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8316878&quot;&gt;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8316878&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14710356" author="mbaesken" created="Fri, 4 Oct 2024 06:51:02 -0700"  >With the patch from &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8340560&quot; title=&quot;Open Source several AWT/2D font and rendering tests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8340560&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8340560&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added the 2 attached images image1.png and image2.png  are created; those seem to differ slightly (at least a diff on command line shows a difference), the test fails because of &amp;quot;Different rendering&amp;quot;.</comment>
